TITLE: Initializing TurnkeyDirectWallet for CosmJS
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to initialize a TurnkeyDirectWallet signer for use with Cosmos-based chains. The code shows setup of the wallet, retrieval of the first account, and extraction of the public key and address. The prefix parameter can be customized for different Cosmos chains.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tkhq/sdk/blob/main/docs/markdown/@turnkey/cosmjs/documents/docs.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Initialize a Turnkey Signer
const turnkeySigner = await TurnkeyDirectWallet.init({
  config: {
    ...
  },
  prefix: "celestia", // can be replaced with other Cosmos chains
});

const account = refineNonNull((await turnkeySigner.getAccounts())[0]);
const compressedPublicKey = toHex(account.pubkey);
const selfAddress = account.address;
```

