TITLE: signCreateSubOrganization Function Definition
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines the `signCreateSubOrganization` function, which takes an input of type `TCreateSubOrganizationInput` and optional `TurnkeyCredentialRequestOptions`. It returns a `Promise` that resolves to a `SignedRequest`. The function is responsible for requesting a WebAuthn assertion and returning a signed request.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tkhq/sdk/blob/main/docs/markdown/@turnkey/http/index/namespaces/TurnkeyApi/functions/signCreateSubOrganization.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
/**
 * Request a WebAuthn assertion and return a signed `CreateSubOrganization` request, ready to be POSTed to Turnkey.
 *
 * See CreateSubOrganization
 *
 * @param input - {@link TCreateSubOrganizationInput}
 * @param options - {@link TurnkeyCredentialRequestOptions}
 * @returns - {@link SignedRequest}
 */

```

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
/** @internal */
export const signCreateSubOrganization = async (
  input: TCreateSubOrganizationInput,
  options?: TurnkeyCredentialRequestOptions
): Promise<SignedRequest> => {
  const method = "POST";
  const url = `/public/v1/organizations/${organizationId()}/sub-organizations/actions/sign_create";

  const { signedRequest } = await signWithWebauthn(
    {
      method,
      url,
      body: input,
    },
    options
  );

  return signedRequest;
};

```

