TITLE: Refreshing Session in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Example of using TurnkeyBrowserClient to refresh an existing, active session and extend its expiry.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tkhq/sdk/blob/main/packages/sdk-browser/documents/docs.md#2025-04-16_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { TurnkeyBrowserClient } from "@turnkey/sdk-browser";

const config = {
  apiBaseUrl: "https://api.turnkey.com",
  defaultOrganizationId: process.env.TURNKEY_ORGANIZATION_ID,
};

// Create a client instance
const browserClient = new TurnkeyBrowserClient(config);

// Refresh the current session
const refreshedSession = await browserClient.refreshSession({
  sessionType: "READ_WRITE",
  expirationSeconds: "900", // 15 minutes
});
```

