TITLE: Authenticating with Passkey in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Example of using TurnkeyBrowserClient to authenticate a user with a Passkey and create a read-write session.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tkhq/sdk/blob/main/packages/sdk-browser/documents/docs.md#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { TurnkeyBrowserClient } from "@turnkey/sdk-browser";

const config = {
  apiBaseUrl: "https://api.turnkey.com",
  defaultOrganizationId: process.env.TURNKEY_ORGANIZATION_ID,
};

// Create a client instance
const browserClient = new TurnkeyBrowserClient(config);
const iframeClient = await turnkeySDK.iframeClient();

// Authenticate with a passkey to create a read-write session
const session = await browserClient.loginWithPasskey({
  sessionType: "READ_WRITE",
  iframeClient: iframeClient,
  expirationSeconds: "900", // 15 minutes
});
```

